    "notes": "Only providers with DISTINCTIVE prefixed token formats are included. Providers whose tokens have no prefix (or share a generic prefix already covered by existing patterns) are documented in s3g_gap_analysis.md as keyword-only. DeepSeek uses sk- identical to OpenAI; not added \u2014 openai_legacy_key already covers that shape. MongoDB/PostgreSQL connection strings already covered by existing connection_string pattern. Snowflake uses account.region.snowflakecomputing.com URIs not caught by current pattern \u2014 a Snowflake-specific pattern added. All examples_match are XOR-encoded per project policy. Updated: added LangSmith (lsv2_pt_/lsv2_sk_) and NVIDIA NIM (nvapi-) from official docs.",
